    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Foliation: Modern foliation added in pencil, upper left recto; catchwords every verso, lower left.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Layout: After the first opening, pages generally laid out in 25 lines per page in 4 columns with gold double rules between each column; border-ruled and page-opening frame-ruled.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Script: Written in nastaʻliq in black ink; pointed.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Decoration: Dual page floriate illuminated first opening in gold, red, and blue with 5 lines of text on cloudbands (f. 1v-2r). Second illuminated header in the same colors (f. 273v). Floriate illuminated panels in gold red and blue across two columns indicate text divisions and appear numerously throughout the manuscript. 119 vividly colored miniatures, mostly half-page size (f. 19v, 23v, 27r, 42r, 45v, 52r, 55v, 57r-57v, 73v, 76r, 77v, 85r, 90r, 95r, 98r, 107r, 122r, 124v, 127v-128r, 132r, 138r, 144r, 146v, 148r, 154r, 156r, 169v, 174r, 179v-180r, 183v, 185r, 188r, 190v, 195v, 201v, 205r-205v, 215v, 217r, 227r-231v [a set of battle images], 235r-235v, 246v, 248v, 253r, 260r, 263v, 265r, 267v, 271v, 272r, 276r, 278v, 280v, 290r, 297r, 299r-299v, 300v, 304r, 306v, 311v, 316r, 318r, 320v, 322r, 324r, 329r, 333v, 336r, 339r, 340r, 342r, 328r, 354r, 355r, 356v, 358v, 363r, 365v, 367r, 371v, 376v, 388r, 395v, 399v, 420v, 431r, 435v, 437r, 441v, 454v, 463r, 473r, 477v, 481r, 484v, 487r, 493r, 499r, 500r, 503r, 507v, 511v, 526v, 530v, 533v). In many of the images, the king resembles Fatḥ-ʻAlī Shāh of the Qajar dynasty.</subfield>
    </datafield>
